 Furthermore, the effect of the population size on the value of ps* is minimal
 compared to that of g (Fig.
 SI).
 Although the population size can affect the strength of selection, it has
 little to no effect on the optimal value of ps.
 Our model also suggests that relatively low switching rates can be sufficient
